    <section ids="gerrit-ssh-setup" names="gerrit\ ssh\ setup">
        <title>Gerrit SSH Setup</title>
        <paragraph>Suppose you have set up Git and Repo on Cygwin before. Copy .ssh from cygwin to the Linux file system root directory:</paragraph>
        <figure ids="ubuntu-wslpath" names="ubuntu-wslpath">
            <image candidates="{'*': 'develop/getting_started/img/wslpath.png'}" original_uri="img/wslpath.png" uri="develop/getting_started/img/wslpath.png" width="300px"></image>
            <caption>Ubutntu WSL Path</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure ids="ubuntu-wsl-directory" names="ubuntu-wsl-directory">
            <image candidates="{'*': 'develop/getting_started/img/wsldirectory.png'}" original_uri="img/wsldirectory.png" uri="develop/getting_started/img/wsldirectory.png" width="300px"></image>
            <caption>Ubutntu WSL Directory</caption>
        </figure>
        <paragraph>Change File Permissions and test configuration</paragraph>
        <literal_block force="False" highlight_args="{}" language="bash" linenos="False" xml:space="preserve">chmod 0600 ~/.ssh/*
ssh gerritgitmaster</literal_block>
        <figure ids="ssh-gerritgitmaster" names="ssh-gerritgitmaster">
            <image candidates="{'*': 'develop/getting_started/img/sshgerrit.png'}" original_uri="img/sshgerrit.png" uri="develop/getting_started/img/sshgerrit.png" width="300px"></image>
            <caption>Test Configuration</caption>
        </figure>
        <paragraph>If it still has permission problem, please try sudo command.</paragraph>
        <target refid="install-required-tools"></target>
    </section>
