        <enumerated_list enumtype="arabic" prefix="" suffix=".">
            <list_item>
                <paragraph>Download, inspect and execute the Kitware archive script to add the Kitware APT repository to your sources list.
                    A detailed explanation of kitware-archive.sh can be found here kitware third-party apt repository:</paragraph>
                <literal_block force="False" highlight_args="{}" language="bash" linenos="False" xml:space="preserve">wget https://apt.kitware.com/kitware-archive.sh
sudo bash kitware-archive.sh</literal_block>
            </list_item>
            <list_item>
                <paragraph>Use <literal>apt</literal> to install the required dependencies:</paragraph>
                <literal_block force="False" highlight_args="{}" language="bash" linenos="False" xml:space="preserve">sudo apt install --no-install-recommends git cmake ninja-build gperf \
  ccache dfu-util device-tree-compiler wget \
  python3-dev python3-pip python3-setuptools python3-tk python3-wheel xz-utils file \
  make gcc gcc-multilib g++-multilib libsdl2-dev perl</literal_block>
            </list_item>
            <list_item>
                <paragraph>Verify the versions of the main dependencies installed on your system by entering:</paragraph>
                <literal_block force="False" highlight_args="{}" language="bash" linenos="False" xml:space="preserve">cmake --version
python3 --version
dtc --version
perl --version</literal_block>
            </list_item>
        </enumerated_list>
        <paragraph>It is suggested to use Python virtual environment if you have other things to do with Ubuntu.</paragraph>
